## Site Configuration

All site info is centralized in `lib/site-config.ts`:

```typescript
import { siteConfig } from '@/lib/site-config'

siteConfig.url           // https://www.notacompany.com
siteConfig.email         // hey@notacompany.com
siteConfig.brandCount    // Dynamic count from MDX files
siteConfig.strings.*     // i18n-ready content strings
```

**Always use `siteConfig`** for:
- URLs (meta, sitemap, robots, llms.txt)
- Meta descriptions
- Site identity (name, email, founder)
- Any text that might need i18n in the future

## Pages

- `app/page.tsx`: Homepage with about section
- `app/portfolio/page.tsx`: Portfolio listing with filters
- `app/portfolio/[slug]/page.tsx`: Individual brand pages

## Development Guidelines

### Code Quality
```bash
pnpm run fix-all       # Auto-fix formatting + linting
pnpm run check-all     # Verify all passes
pnpm run build         # Generates llms.txt + builds production
```

### Code Style
- TypeScript with strict settings
- Server Components preferred
- Minimal dependencies
- Simple, readable code

### Content Guidelines
- First person ("I" not "we")
- Human, approachable tone
- No corporate speak or buzzwords
- Keep it simple and honest

## Key Files

- `lib/site-config.ts`: **Centralized site config** (URL, strings, i18n)
- `lib/brands.ts`: Brand data utilities
- `app/globals.css`: Classic HTML styling (Times, blue links, hr)
- `content/brands/`: MDX files with brand info
- `scripts/generate-llms-txt.ts`: Generates LLMs.txt files on build
- `public/llms.txt`: LLM context file (auto-generated)
- `public/brands/`: LLM-readable brand files (auto-generated)

## SEO Configuration

Each page sets its own canonical URL via `alternates.canonical`:

```typescript
// In each page's metadata export
export const metadata: Metadata = {
  alternates: {
    canonical: '/portfolio',  // Relative path, resolved against metadataBase
  },
}
```

**Important SEO rules:**
- Do NOT set canonical in root `layout.tsx` (it overrides all pages)
- Each page must set its own canonical URL
- Use `siteConfig.url` as `metadataBase` in root layout
- Brand links must be server-rendered for crawlers (not client-only)

## Important Notes

- **No OG meta tags** - keeping it minimal
- **No fancy UI components** - pure HTML aesthetic
- **Static generation** for all pages
- **LLMs.txt auto-generated** - runs on `pnpm run build`
- **Dynamic brand count** - no hardcoded "16 brands"
- **Per-page canonicals** - each page sets its own canonical URL
- Footer credits: world's first website + GitHub links

